WEBVTT

00:01.869 --> 00:04.638
Good news. I have a VIP
who needs a multiple ligament

00:04.672 --> 00:07.041
reconstruction on his elbow,
and I've got room

00:07.075 --> 00:09.810
for a couple residents
to assist me and Dr. Melendez.

00:09.843 --> 00:10.811
Awesome.

00:10.844 --> 00:13.414
I've never assisted
on one of those before.

00:13.447 --> 00:14.482
Dr. Andrews
knows that.

00:14.515 --> 00:16.284
That's why he's acting
like it's Christmas morning.

00:16.317 --> 00:17.351
I'm guessing you've
never operated

00:17.385 --> 00:19.153
on a pro athlete, either.

00:19.187 --> 00:20.654
[ Jared clears throat ]
Um, last time I checked,

00:20.688 --> 00:23.191
a "couple" means "two,"
and there's three of us.

00:23.224 --> 00:24.292
More good news.

00:24.325 --> 00:27.828
Whoever isn't with us
will be assisting Dr. Coyle

00:27.861 --> 00:29.763
on a double-leg
fasciotomy.

00:29.797 --> 00:30.664
[ Chuckles ]

00:30.698 --> 00:32.366
[ Claps hands ]
Andrews: Feeling lucky?

00:34.368 --> 00:36.104
Murphy.

00:36.137 --> 00:39.107
VIP elbow. Sweet.

00:41.342 --> 00:43.444
[ Sighs ] Fasciotomy.

00:43.477 --> 00:44.312
Whoo.

00:46.214 --> 00:48.116
Bobby Ato?
Don't think I've heard of him.

00:48.149 --> 00:49.550
He's a pro athlete?

00:49.583 --> 00:51.285
He's a pro. I don't know
if I'd call him in athlete.

00:51.319 --> 00:53.354
-E-sports.
-[ Chuckles ]

00:53.387 --> 00:54.388
Video games?

00:54.422 --> 00:55.223
He's one of the best
in the world.

00:55.256 --> 00:56.524
Last year,
he won enough prize money

00:56.557 --> 00:58.726
to buy his mom a beach house
in Monterey.

00:58.759 --> 01:00.261
Paid cash.

01:00.294 --> 01:03.097
Is he considered
a very important person

01:03.131 --> 01:05.833
because he's an athlete or
because he has a lot of money?

01:05.866 --> 01:06.867
Both.Both.

01:06.900 --> 01:08.802
[ Elevator bell dings ]
Mm.

01:08.836 --> 01:11.639
[ Indistinct announcement
over P.A. ]

01:11.672 --> 01:15.576
**

01:15.609 --> 01:17.811
I have to go.

01:23.817 --> 01:26.220
Morning, Shaun.

01:26.254 --> 01:28.122
This is Melissa Bourne,

01:28.156 --> 01:31.125
the therapist
that we talked about.

01:31.159 --> 01:35.463
That you agreed
to meet with, right, Shaun?

01:35.496 --> 01:37.365
Hi, Shaun.
It's nice to meet you.

01:38.899 --> 01:40.434
H-H-Hi.

01:40.468 --> 01:41.902
Dr. Glassman thought
it would be a good idea

01:41.935 --> 01:44.272
for us to meet before
our first in-home session.

01:44.305 --> 01:45.873
Just to make sure
you're comfortable.

01:45.906 --> 01:47.575
I am not comfortable.

01:47.608 --> 01:50.144
Shaun [Sighs]

01:50.178 --> 01:51.312
It's gonna be fine.

01:51.345 --> 01:53.314
You two are going
to like each other.

01:53.347 --> 01:56.917
Dr. Bourne has a PhD
in cognitive psychology.

01:56.950 --> 01:59.520
She can really help you, but
you have to give her a chance.

01:59.553 --> 02:03.624
**

02:03.657 --> 02:05.193
Okay?

02:07.595 --> 02:08.829
'Kay. Okay.

02:08.862 --> 02:10.898
I'm proud of you, Shaun.

02:10.931 --> 02:13.301
I'm already proud of you.

02:13.334 --> 02:23.311
**

02:23.344 --> 02:25.746
**

02:25.779 --> 02:28.749
-- Captions by VITAC --

02:28.782 --> 02:35.289
**

02:36.590 --> 02:39.527
Notice the separation
at zero degrees.

02:39.560 --> 02:43.364
It's indicative of complete
tears of the LCL and the UCL.

02:43.397 --> 02:45.366
A perfect candidate
for surgery.

02:45.399 --> 02:48.202
How's your mom?
Still beating cancer?

02:48.236 --> 02:49.637
Oh, she's good, bro.

02:49.670 --> 02:51.539
She said she gets checked out
at the beach all the time

02:51.572 --> 02:53.241
ever since you did
her breast reconstruction.

02:53.274 --> 02:55.676
So, uh, thanks.
[ Chuckles ] I guess.

02:55.709 --> 02:57.878
We're gonna take
good care of you.

02:57.911 --> 02:59.680
See you in the O.R.
Thank you.

02:59.713 --> 03:02.250
Which part of the UCL is the
principal secondary restraint

03:02.283 --> 03:03.651
to excessive
valgus movement?

03:03.684 --> 03:05.553
-Anterior.
-Everything okay?

03:05.586 --> 03:06.954
Yes, I'm fine.

03:08.456 --> 03:09.790
I'm fine.

03:12.726 --> 03:13.961
Squeeze my hands.

03:18.499 --> 03:28.476
**

03:28.509 --> 03:37.017
**

03:37.050 --> 03:41.889
There is a paradoxical loss
of grip strength on the left.

03:41.922 --> 03:45.626
There are many possible
explanations for that,

03:45.659 --> 03:48.562
one of which i--
One of which is...

03:48.596 --> 03:50.264
he has ligament tears
in his left arm.

03:50.298 --> 03:52.566
The anesthesiologist
will be up in a few

03:52.600 --> 03:54.034
to get you ready
for surgery.

03:54.067 --> 03:55.803
Dope. Thank you.

04:00.774 --> 04:03.477
Uh, Dr. Murphy.

04:03.511 --> 04:05.413
What's wrong with you?
-N-Nothing.

04:05.446 --> 04:07.781
I have
a condition called --

04:07.815 --> 04:09.917
You're autistic.
Yeah, yeah, yeah. Mm, I get it.

04:09.950 --> 04:12.620
But what is wrong with you,
bro?

04:12.653 --> 04:16.490
You gotta be legit smart
to land a gig as a surgeon

04:16.524 --> 04:20.361
and he just shut you down
like a noob.

04:20.394 --> 04:24.465
I'll bring the idea up again.
I do that.

04:24.498 --> 04:25.899
They don't respect you.

04:27.535 --> 04:29.770
And they should listen to you
the first time.

04:29.803 --> 04:32.373
-I can't control what they do.
-Of course you can.

04:32.406 --> 04:33.707
That's what playing the game
is all about.

04:33.741 --> 04:35.509
It's about controlling
your opponent.

04:35.543 --> 04:37.044
You gotta find
the right strategy.

04:37.077 --> 04:38.612
It is not a game.

04:38.646 --> 04:41.382
Everything's a game, man.
Everything's a game.

04:41.415 --> 04:42.916
Just sometimes
the stakes are higher,

04:42.950 --> 04:45.519
and this time it's my arm.

04:45.553 --> 04:49.757
**

04:49.790 --> 04:52.693
[ Indistinct announcement
over P.A. ]

04:52.726 --> 04:55.062
So, I'm guessing
you drew the short straw.

04:55.095 --> 04:57.097
I beg your pardon?
Well, you're here

04:57.130 --> 04:58.932
and your co-residents
are on the VIP case.

04:58.966 --> 05:01.935
I'm awesome and I'd still rather
be with Melendez and Andrews.

05:01.969 --> 05:04.538
-No, it's fine --
-Relax. It's cool.

05:04.572 --> 05:06.073
Tell me about our patient.

05:06.106 --> 05:08.075
Uh, 34-year-old female,
software engineer

05:08.108 --> 05:10.344
and entrepreneur presenting
with Compartment Syndrome

05:10.378 --> 05:12.780
caused by extreme overexertion
at a spin class.

05:12.813 --> 05:14.682
The condition has caused
the muscles in her legs to --

05:14.715 --> 05:16.684
-Okay. Great.
-I wasn't finished.

05:16.717 --> 05:18.886
Finished enough to show me
you're smart and thorough.

05:18.919 --> 05:19.987
You know
the treatment plan?

05:20.020 --> 05:21.389
We need to make
incisions on --

05:21.422 --> 05:23.691
Good.

05:23.724 --> 05:25.593
You take lead.

05:28.962 --> 05:30.964
[ Hazel winces ]

05:32.933 --> 05:34.902
We need to make a number
of long incisions

05:34.935 --> 05:38.071
down both sides of each leg
to relieve the tension

05:38.105 --> 05:40.774
and return
healthy circulation.

05:40.808 --> 05:42.376
It's important
we act quickly.

05:42.410 --> 05:44.512
If we don't get the swelling
under control,

05:44.545 --> 05:46.146
the damage
could be irreparable.

05:46.179 --> 05:48.849
What does that mean?
I could lose my legs?

05:48.882 --> 05:50.684
From working out too hard
in a spin class?

05:50.718 --> 05:53.086
No, don't worry. Your sister's
gonna be just fine.

05:53.120 --> 05:55.689
Look, I'm very confident
we caught this in time.

05:55.723 --> 05:56.957
[ Sighs ]

05:56.990 --> 05:58.659
If you could
lean forward?

05:58.692 --> 06:01.128
I just need to check your
kidneys haven't been affected.

06:01.161 --> 06:03.964
Let me know if you have
any tenderness.

06:03.997 --> 06:06.600
[ Tapping ]

06:06.634 --> 06:10.671
**

06:10.704 --> 06:12.906
Extracting
the palmaris now.

06:17.645 --> 06:21.649
[ Drill whirring ]

06:21.682 --> 06:24.552
Dr. Andrews, I read
your op-ed in Gen Surge News.

06:24.585 --> 06:26.554
Brilliant piece.

06:26.587 --> 06:28.822
Never realized the lack
of continuity of care

06:28.856 --> 06:30.591
was such a severe problem.

06:32.793 --> 06:34.928
Dr. Melendez...

06:34.962 --> 06:36.964
you have
very beautiful hair.

06:38.632 --> 06:39.433
Thank you.

06:39.467 --> 06:41.835
Given the patient's
grip weakness,

06:41.869 --> 06:43.971
we could do
a nerve conduction test

06:44.004 --> 06:46.173
to rule out
any concurrent nerve damage.

06:46.206 --> 06:47.575
No.

06:49.610 --> 06:52.112
Okay, that looks like
a good stopping point.

06:52.145 --> 06:54.982
Dr. Kalu...step in.

06:56.016 --> 06:58.519
-Something wrong?
-No, it looks good.

06:58.552 --> 07:00.120
I just want to give Dr. Kalu
an opportunity

07:00.153 --> 07:01.822
to show us what he can do.

07:01.855 --> 07:03.123
As long as that's okay
with you.

07:04.091 --> 07:05.158
Sure.

07:05.192 --> 07:07.528
-Thank you, Dr. Andrews.
-Mm-hmm.

07:07.561 --> 07:12.566
**

07:12.600 --> 07:15.503
[ Drill whirring ]

07:26.914 --> 07:29.617
All right, looking good.

07:29.650 --> 07:32.085
Let's move
to the lateral side.

07:32.119 --> 07:34.154
So, what are we doing tonight,
ladies?

07:34.187 --> 07:36.757
How about we go
to Viva's?

07:36.790 --> 07:38.559
Sounds good.

07:38.592 --> 07:39.827
Bovie.

07:41.161 --> 07:43.130
You're awfully quiet over there,
Dr. Browne.

07:43.163 --> 07:44.832
I'm just focused.

07:44.865 --> 07:46.600
I know you're used
to operating with Melendez,

07:46.634 --> 07:49.069
but we have fun here.

07:49.102 --> 07:50.604
I feel like
when it's less tense,

07:50.638 --> 07:52.540
people make
fewer mistakes.

07:52.573 --> 07:54.207
Okay.

07:54.241 --> 07:55.909
You wanna take
the other leg?

07:57.310 --> 08:00.113
Really?
Yeah, best way to learn
is by doing it, right?

08:00.147 --> 08:01.882
Definitely.

08:01.915 --> 08:02.950
So go for it.

08:07.755 --> 08:14.695
**

08:14.728 --> 08:21.669
**

08:21.702 --> 08:28.609
**

08:28.642 --> 08:31.178
[ "Ordinary Man" by Eels plays ]

08:31.211 --> 08:36.784
**

08:36.817 --> 08:42.756
**

08:42.790 --> 08:46.326
* Well, it's another warm day

08:46.359 --> 08:49.930
* In the city of cold hearts

08:49.963 --> 08:54.167
* They all just play the part
of who they are *

08:54.201 --> 08:56.169
[ Cellphone chimes ]

08:56.203 --> 09:00.173
* And I'm here on my own

09:00.207 --> 09:03.811
* I'd rather be alone

09:03.844 --> 09:08.548
* Than try to be someone
that I'm not *

09:10.684 --> 09:18.659
* And you seem like someone
who could appreciate the fact *

09:18.692 --> 09:22.730
* That I'm no ordinary man

09:28.902 --> 09:36.977
**

09:40.848 --> 09:42.683
Shaun, good morning.

09:42.716 --> 09:44.852
Good morning,
Dr. Glassman.

09:46.386 --> 09:48.088
How'd it go with Melissa?

09:48.121 --> 09:49.757
She was...

09:49.790 --> 09:51.659
very helpful.

09:51.692 --> 09:52.760
[ Elevator bell dings ]

09:52.793 --> 09:54.928
You're wearing the same clothes
as yesterday, Shaun.

09:54.962 --> 09:57.097
After you.

10:05.673 --> 10:08.676
Apparently we are
at an impasse.

10:08.709 --> 10:11.745
I feel strongly that Melissa
can be very helpful to you.

10:11.779 --> 10:14.214
You feel so strongly
that she can't

10:14.247 --> 10:15.348
that you're willing
to sacrifice

10:15.382 --> 10:17.951
a good night's sleep
and hygiene.

10:17.985 --> 10:20.020
Shaun, you smell.

10:23.757 --> 10:26.727
I will shower
in the doctor's lounge.

10:26.760 --> 10:30.030
Well, great.
That solves one problem.

10:30.063 --> 10:33.133
You stayed here all night
just to avoid a confrontation.

10:33.166 --> 10:35.202
Just say "no," Shaun.

10:35.235 --> 10:36.369
You know? Just say "no."

10:36.403 --> 10:38.739
No!

10:38.772 --> 10:39.873
No.

10:39.907 --> 10:42.676
[ Sighs ]
Great. That's just great.

10:42.710 --> 10:44.011
I don't have
to see Melissa?

10:44.044 --> 10:46.714
No, you don't have
to see Melissa.

10:46.747 --> 10:48.882
You're a grown man.
You can make your own decisions.

10:48.916 --> 10:52.319
I just happen to feel that she
could be of great help to you.

10:52.352 --> 10:54.888
That [Scoffs]

10:54.922 --> 10:57.224
I'll tell you what.

10:57.257 --> 10:58.926
You see Melissa
three times

10:58.959 --> 11:01.194
and I will buy you
the surround-sound system

11:01.228 --> 11:03.196
you want
for your television.

11:03.230 --> 11:04.431
Are you bribing me?

11:04.464 --> 11:06.934
I suppose I am.

11:08.401 --> 11:10.103
If you don't like her,
she'll leave.

11:10.137 --> 11:13.874
And I promise I will never say
another word about it.

11:13.907 --> 11:15.876
That's a pretty good deal.

11:15.909 --> 11:17.745
[ Elevator bell dings ]

11:17.778 --> 11:21.181
**

11:21.214 --> 11:22.382
Okay.

11:22.415 --> 11:24.051
Okay.

11:25.753 --> 11:27.454
I will meet with her
tonight.

11:27.487 --> 11:29.189
That's good, Shaun.

11:29.222 --> 11:34.795
**

11:34.828 --> 11:36.964
[ Inhales sharply ]

11:41.001 --> 11:44.204
Saline? I've never seen it
done quite like that.

11:44.237 --> 11:46.940
Yeah, I had a professor
from Portugal.

11:46.974 --> 11:50.143
Apparently it's how they do it
over there.

11:50.177 --> 11:52.012
It's supposed
to lessen the pain.

11:52.045 --> 11:54.047
Well, the good news is
your tissue is nice and pink,

11:54.081 --> 11:55.348
which means it's healthy.

11:55.382 --> 11:56.917
Unfortunately,
the swelling is not

11:56.950 --> 11:58.351
coming down
like we'd hoped.

11:58.385 --> 12:00.921
Does this mean you're going
to have to amputate?

12:00.954 --> 12:03.256
No, no.
Sometimes it just takes time.

12:03.290 --> 12:04.324
We'll take care of you.

12:04.357 --> 12:06.059
[ Sighs ]

12:06.093 --> 12:08.361
Very nice work,
Dr. Browne.

12:08.395 --> 12:17.771
**

12:17.805 --> 12:19.039
Hey.

12:19.072 --> 12:21.942
Can you do me a solid
and trade patients?

12:21.975 --> 12:24.311
No, not a chance.
Andrews let me take lead.

12:24.344 --> 12:26.246
Coyle let me take lead,
too.

12:26.279 --> 12:28.481
So what is the problem?

12:28.515 --> 12:30.818
He's a little
too friendly.

12:33.186 --> 12:34.988
He patted my back
in a weird way.

12:35.022 --> 12:36.790
I don't know.
It was -- It was awkward.

12:36.824 --> 12:38.959
I'm sure he's just trying
to establish a rapport.

12:40.327 --> 12:41.795
Maybe?

12:41.829 --> 12:43.897
I don't...

12:43.931 --> 12:45.833
Shaun? Switch?

12:45.866 --> 12:47.200
Shaun: No.

12:47.234 --> 12:49.002
I like Bobby.

12:49.036 --> 12:51.038
He has very good advice.

12:51.071 --> 12:55.442
**

12:55.475 --> 12:57.010
So, who did what?

12:57.044 --> 12:58.979
Well,
I did, uh, most of the surgery

12:59.012 --> 13:00.180
along with Dr. Andrews

13:00.213 --> 13:02.950
and Dr. Kalu aided in replacing
one of your torn ligaments.

13:02.983 --> 13:05.318
You should be back
in competition shape
in a few weeks time.

13:05.352 --> 13:07.054
Word. [ Chuckles ]

13:07.087 --> 13:08.922
What about you?
What'd you do?

13:08.956 --> 13:12.893
I helped to clean
the grafted tendons.

13:12.926 --> 13:14.895
Ah. That's it.

13:14.928 --> 13:16.830
Yes.

13:16.864 --> 13:18.231
Come on.
You didn't get up in there?

13:22.535 --> 13:26.406
Y-Your muscle weakness

13:26.439 --> 13:29.276
along with
the high body temperature

13:29.309 --> 13:32.913
could be an early indicator
of multiple sclerosis.

13:36.116 --> 13:37.918
We should order an MRI.

13:37.951 --> 13:40.053
We have talked about this
countless times.

13:40.087 --> 13:42.589
Yes.
We should order an MRI.

13:42.622 --> 13:44.391
We are not ordering
an MRI.

13:44.424 --> 13:45.893
You don't respect me.

13:45.926 --> 13:47.294
Not right now, I don't.

13:47.327 --> 13:49.162
Dr. Andrews, Dr. Melendez.

13:49.196 --> 13:50.630
Given the fact we're dealing
with a pro athlete,

13:50.663 --> 13:53.066
even the slightest hiccup
could be problematic.

13:53.100 --> 13:56.536
I think Bobby would be impressed
by our being extra attentive.

13:58.038 --> 13:59.206
Kalu is right --
he is a pro athlete

13:59.239 --> 14:00.407
in his prime earning years.

14:00.440 --> 14:03.877
We should make sure
we leave him 100%.

14:03.911 --> 14:08.015
**

14:08.048 --> 14:09.182
Do the MRI.

14:13.921 --> 14:16.523
Nice score.
You got 'em to listen.

14:16.556 --> 14:18.325
Do the MRI.

14:18.358 --> 14:21.228
No, Jared did.

14:21.261 --> 14:23.596
How did he get there
when you couldn't?

14:23.630 --> 14:25.298
He asked nicely.

14:25.332 --> 14:27.300
Okay, you asked nicely.

14:27.334 --> 14:30.503
Yes. Yes, I did.

14:30.537 --> 14:33.140
You gotta be fierce
if you want the glory, bro.

14:33.173 --> 14:34.407
Oh, no.

14:34.441 --> 14:37.077
I do not want the glory,
bro.

14:37.110 --> 14:39.646
I just want
to be a good surgeon.

14:39.679 --> 14:41.114
Everyone wants glory.

14:41.148 --> 14:42.950
It -- It's how you get
what you want.

14:42.983 --> 14:45.953
And everybody's got wants.

14:45.986 --> 14:50.423
I want a surround-sound
speaker system.

14:52.059 --> 14:54.094
To get it,
I have to see a therapist.

14:54.127 --> 14:56.296
I don't want to have
to see a therapist.

14:56.329 --> 15:00.500
Okay, yeah, that's --
that's how I got my first PS2.

15:00.533 --> 15:02.469
Yeah, my parents bribed me
to go to therapy

15:02.502 --> 15:03.703
after they split up.

15:03.736 --> 15:05.638
What was therapy like?

15:05.672 --> 15:06.639
Pretty basic, bro.

15:06.673 --> 15:07.640
She'd tell me what to do,

15:07.674 --> 15:08.708
how to deal
with my parents.

15:08.741 --> 15:10.143
Was it helpful?

15:10.177 --> 15:11.278
I don't know.

15:11.311 --> 15:14.014
I never did anything
she told me to do.

15:14.047 --> 15:16.349
Is that an option?

15:16.383 --> 15:18.952
Doing whatever the hell
you feel like doing

15:18.986 --> 15:20.553
is alway an option.

15:20.587 --> 15:26.359
**

15:26.393 --> 15:29.729
[ Clears throat ]
Just a gentle reminder --

15:29.762 --> 15:31.431
dinner with my dad
tonight at 8:00.

15:31.464 --> 15:32.665
It is on my calendar.

15:32.699 --> 15:34.234
So was
the Gypsy Kings concert,

15:34.267 --> 15:36.203
and I --
I seem to remember...

15:36.236 --> 15:38.238
Fair enough.

15:38.271 --> 15:40.373
How is the VIP case?

15:40.407 --> 15:43.310
Shaun seems off
about something.

15:43.343 --> 15:44.311
Did you talk to him?

15:44.344 --> 15:46.579
Yes. Because talking
to Shaun solves problems.

15:46.613 --> 15:48.348
And Andrews is...

15:48.381 --> 15:49.682
He's a pain in your ass.

15:49.716 --> 15:52.285
No.
He's actually too friendly.

15:52.319 --> 15:55.055
Jared kisses his ass
and suddenly he's cutting.

15:55.088 --> 15:58.458
Well, ass kissing
is a useful skill for a surgeon.

15:58.491 --> 16:00.027
That's a very
beautiful blouse.

16:00.060 --> 16:01.228
[ Laughing ] Do I still have
to go to dinner?

16:01.261 --> 16:02.629
Yes.
It'll be nice.

16:02.662 --> 16:05.465
You'll have some nice wine
and my dad will pay.

16:05.498 --> 16:07.200
He'll push us
to set a wedding date.

16:07.234 --> 16:08.335
April 25th.

16:08.368 --> 16:09.402
Did you book something?

16:09.436 --> 16:10.537
No.

16:10.570 --> 16:14.074
But my dad doesn't need
to know that.

16:14.107 --> 16:16.743
[ Indistinct announcement
over P.A. ]

16:16.776 --> 16:18.278
What do you got?

16:18.311 --> 16:21.214
Looks like the surgically
repaired elbow is fine.

16:21.248 --> 16:22.215
As I suspected.

16:22.249 --> 16:24.384
But Murphy noticed something
in the periphery,

16:24.417 --> 16:26.253
a little higher up,
just above the bicep.

16:26.286 --> 16:28.088
It was my idea.

16:28.121 --> 16:30.523
Yes,
I just said that.

16:30.557 --> 16:34.127
So, we took an image from
higher up and noticed this.

16:36.129 --> 16:39.599
It's encasing the entirety
of his brachial plexus.

16:44.304 --> 16:46.106
This thing is massive.

16:46.139 --> 16:48.308
Biopsy indicated
it's definitely a schwannoma.

16:48.341 --> 16:50.710
And it's definitely
malignant.

16:50.743 --> 16:53.513
It's in a tricky spot, but you
might be able to remove it.

16:53.546 --> 16:56.816
Follow it up with a combo
of radiotherapy and chemo

16:56.849 --> 16:58.185
to finish it o...

17:00.253 --> 17:01.688
What?
What's the problem?

17:01.721 --> 17:05.392
Robert Ato. Bobby Ato.
Pro-gamer Bobby Ato?

17:05.425 --> 17:06.393
You a fan?

17:06.426 --> 17:07.694
I met three years ago.

17:07.727 --> 17:10.163
Oncology consult
for SF Muni.

17:12.599 --> 17:15.102
He had cancer
three years ago?

17:15.135 --> 17:19.206
**

17:22.175 --> 17:25.078
Why the hell wouldn't
you tell us that you
had already had cancer?

17:25.112 --> 17:26.113
It was in my lower leg
three years ago.

17:26.146 --> 17:28.115
How's that gonna change
how you fix my elbow?

17:28.148 --> 17:30.183
It would have a huge effect
on how I viewed the symptoms

17:30.217 --> 17:31.318
that Dr. Murphy noticed.

17:31.351 --> 17:33.386
[ Scoffs ] You didn't listen
to Dr. Murphy

17:33.420 --> 17:34.821
because you don't
respect him.

17:34.854 --> 17:36.223
'Cause Dr. Murphy
is different.

17:36.256 --> 17:37.424
I respect him.

17:37.457 --> 17:39.292
He has good ideas,
and he has bad ideas.

17:39.326 --> 17:41.294
Turns out this was a good one.
That you shot down.

17:41.328 --> 17:44.431
Why did you
hide the truth?

17:44.464 --> 17:47.800
A previous cancer diagnosis
isn't shameful.

17:50.870 --> 17:53.540
[ Chuckles ]

17:53.573 --> 17:55.275
[ Exhales sharply ]

17:55.308 --> 17:57.444
After the first diagnosis,

17:57.477 --> 18:00.780
all I was thinking was,
"Will it come back?

18:00.813 --> 18:03.450
How bad will it be?"

18:03.483 --> 18:04.584
I was distracted, man.

18:04.617 --> 18:07.120
I couldn't focus,
and I hit a slump --

18:07.154 --> 18:08.355
Wait, you were worried
that cancer

18:08.388 --> 18:09.589
was messing
with your gaming?

18:09.622 --> 18:11.658
Yeah, man!

18:11.691 --> 18:13.393
It cost me a championship.

18:13.426 --> 18:16.329
I decided to block it out
along with all the thoughts

18:16.363 --> 18:18.198
of negativity
and physical weakness,

18:18.231 --> 18:22.101
and like that,
I became the best in the world.

18:25.672 --> 18:28.741
We need to do
a full-body scan

18:28.775 --> 18:31.744
to make sure the cancer
has not already metastasized.

18:31.778 --> 18:34.247
What he said.

18:37.184 --> 18:38.885
What I said.

18:40.187 --> 18:43.290
This looks great.

18:43.323 --> 18:45.458
The swelling is starting
to reduce.

18:45.492 --> 18:46.859
We can start tightening
the sutures.

18:46.893 --> 18:50.597
[ Sighs ]
Finally some good news.

18:50.630 --> 18:52.432
You look like
you're doing better, too...

18:52.465 --> 18:55.168
now your boss is gone.

18:55.202 --> 18:58.271
Dr. Coyle? He's fine.

18:58.305 --> 19:00.240
You don't have to toe
the party line with me.

19:00.273 --> 19:02.275
Trust me. I get it.

19:02.309 --> 19:05.478
I almost rode myself to death
in a spin class

19:05.512 --> 19:07.247
because I overheard
a couple of investors say

19:07.280 --> 19:10.317
that they "liked the concept
just fine,"

19:10.350 --> 19:12.852
but that my cankles
were "too distracting."

19:12.885 --> 19:15.822
What?
Your idea is brilliant.

19:15.855 --> 19:18.591
And you're beautiful.
Screw those jackasses.

19:18.625 --> 19:20.493
[ Laughs ] Grace,
you don't get it.

19:20.527 --> 19:23.396
You got the face, perfect little
hip-to-waist ratio,

19:23.430 --> 19:25.932
and most VC firms
are run by a bunch of bros,

19:25.965 --> 19:27.600
so there is
an inverse relationship

19:27.634 --> 19:30.603
between the size of my ass
and how much money I can raise.

19:30.637 --> 19:31.871
Then you should
do something else

19:31.904 --> 19:33.840
where you don't have
to deal with bros.

19:33.873 --> 19:35.508
Like what, become a nun?

19:35.542 --> 19:37.277
[ Chuckles ]

19:37.310 --> 19:39.312
-Sorry.
-You agree with her?

19:39.346 --> 19:40.713
She nearly worked
herself to death

19:40.747 --> 19:42.915
trying to please
some pigs with money?

19:42.949 --> 19:43.850
She shouldn't have to.

19:43.883 --> 19:45.985
Great. Let me know
when you find utopia.

19:46.018 --> 19:48.888
But until then,
I love what I do.

19:48.921 --> 19:51.624
So I got to play the game
'cause if I call them out,

19:51.658 --> 19:55.795
I just get labeled a "bitch,"
or even worse.

19:55.828 --> 19:57.230
Your heart rate's
going up.

19:57.264 --> 19:58.231
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

19:58.265 --> 19:59.499
-[ Gasping ]
-Hazel?

19:59.532 --> 20:01.768
Hazel?

20:01.801 --> 20:03.703
She's barely moving
any air.

20:03.736 --> 20:05.472
Hazel,
can you hear me?

20:05.505 --> 20:07.407
Code blue!
I need to intubate her.

20:07.440 --> 20:09.108
Give me a laryngoscope
and an ET tube.

20:09.141 --> 20:11.778
Let's get her on 100% oxygen.
Woman on P.A.: Code blue.
4 North, room 407.

20:11.811 --> 20:14.614
Code blue.
4 North, room 407.

20:14.647 --> 20:17.917
**

20:17.950 --> 20:18.918
Talk to me.

20:18.951 --> 20:19.719
Her lungs --

20:19.752 --> 20:22.389
I think it's
a reperfusion injury.

20:22.422 --> 20:24.424
[ Scoffs ]
There's no room in here.

20:24.457 --> 20:26.893
Mallampati 3, maybe 4.
You should take over.

20:26.926 --> 20:29.762
You're doing fine.
Here, use the bougie.

20:29.796 --> 20:34.467
[ Beeping continues ]

20:34.501 --> 20:36.403
You feel the epiglottis?
-I think so.

20:36.436 --> 20:38.538
Okay, go a bit further,
you should feel it stop.

20:38.571 --> 20:39.939
If it keeps going,
you're in the esophagus.

20:39.972 --> 20:42.442
It stopped, got it.
ET tube?

20:46.012 --> 20:48.381
[ Beeping slows ]
It's gonna be okay.

20:52.852 --> 20:53.986
Strong work, Doctor.

20:58.691 --> 21:00.693
Best in the world or not,
this guy's insane.

21:00.727 --> 21:03.496
Hiding from a diagnosis?
[ Scoffs ]

21:03.530 --> 21:07.567
Doesn't work --
it'll find you.

21:07.600 --> 21:11.571
Bobby wanted to be the best.
He is the best.

21:11.604 --> 21:12.805
I don't think he was
trying to be the best.

21:12.839 --> 21:13.940
I think
he was just scared.

21:13.973 --> 21:16.876
What's that?
Next to the brain stem.

21:16.909 --> 21:21.581
**

21:21.614 --> 21:24.617
Oh, another schwannoma.

21:25.918 --> 21:28.521
So much for the power
of positive thinking.

21:35.362 --> 21:37.930
He's a strange kid.
He had cancer.

21:37.964 --> 21:40.533
Stopped going to follow-ups
because he started losing.

21:40.567 --> 21:41.401
What's so strange?

21:41.434 --> 21:43.870
Sounds like a classic case
of denial.

21:44.637 --> 21:45.905
I was thinking we could try
something new.

21:45.938 --> 21:46.973
Maybe gamma knife?

21:47.006 --> 21:49.909
I don't think so.
Wrong type of tumor for that.

21:51.811 --> 21:53.346
What if I told you
every few months

21:53.380 --> 21:56.916
that you had a real possibility
you were gonna die?

21:56.949 --> 22:00.420
I'd be scared.
And I'd listen.

22:00.453 --> 22:02.855
Maybe you would,
maybe you wouldn't.

22:02.889 --> 22:04.023
Personally,
I think he's right --

22:04.056 --> 22:05.658
shut down
those voices of doom,

22:05.692 --> 22:08.094
spend your days living
instead of dying.

22:08.127 --> 22:09.962
But he may also be crazy.

22:12.432 --> 22:13.600
Short of making him
a vegetable,

22:13.633 --> 22:15.735
I don't know if there's anything
we can do.

22:20.072 --> 22:22.442
Is -- Is Shaun okay?

22:24.411 --> 22:25.645
Is his work okay?

22:25.678 --> 22:26.879
Yes, I just, um --

22:26.913 --> 22:28.147
Then he's fine.

22:28.180 --> 22:36.756
**

22:36.789 --> 22:38.157
[ Door closes ]

22:38.190 --> 22:44.063
**

22:48.167 --> 22:49.802
[ Laughing ] Damn.

22:49.836 --> 22:51.003
[ Normal voice ]
Horse walks into a bar.

22:51.037 --> 22:54.607
Bartender says...

22:54.641 --> 22:56.108
We found another mass.

22:56.142 --> 22:59.812
That's not how it goes,
but cool.

22:59.846 --> 23:00.747
Let's knock it out,
too.

23:00.780 --> 23:02.982
The mass is located
on your brain stem.

23:03.015 --> 23:06.018
Which controls
your autonomic nervous system --

23:06.052 --> 23:08.621
your heart,
respiration.

23:08.655 --> 23:11.424
Its positioning
makes it inoperable.

23:11.458 --> 23:17.964
**

23:17.997 --> 23:21.834
**

23:21.868 --> 23:26.673
I...had a good run.

23:26.706 --> 23:32.011
Wish it was longer,
but...

23:32.044 --> 23:34.581
I'm gonna go out
on top.

23:36.916 --> 23:39.719
If you went out today,

23:39.752 --> 23:42.822
could you say
the same thing?

23:42.855 --> 23:47.927
**

23:47.960 --> 23:50.630
[ Monitor beeping,
papers rustling ]

23:53.733 --> 23:55.902
She's lucky
you were there.

23:55.935 --> 23:58.538
Me?
You're the one who saved her.

23:58.571 --> 24:00.707
With your help.
A lot of it.

24:00.740 --> 24:02.642
So, thank you.

24:05.578 --> 24:07.780
Hey, look, you wanna --
you wanna get a drink?

24:07.814 --> 24:09.015
Maybe take
the edge off?

24:09.048 --> 24:12.151
No.
But thank you, though.

24:12.184 --> 24:15.154
Are you sure?
I promise you'll have fun.

24:15.187 --> 24:17.624
I give great massages.

24:17.657 --> 24:19.692
And I'll make a killer omelet
in the morning.

24:19.726 --> 24:21.561
[ Scoffs ]

24:21.594 --> 24:23.663
That's really
inappropriate.

24:23.696 --> 24:25.665
I said no.

24:25.698 --> 24:28.234
I'm sorry. W-W-- [Scoffs]
Where's this coming from?

24:28.267 --> 24:30.036
You were -- You were clearly
giving me signals.

24:30.069 --> 24:31.037
No, the only "signal"
I gave you

24:31.070 --> 24:34.541
was that I wasn't interested
in the slightest.

24:34.574 --> 24:36.275
Okay, see, I just --
I heard about you and Kalu

24:36.308 --> 24:38.044
banging in the call room,
so I figured --

24:38.077 --> 24:40.580
This conversation is over.
You're an ass.

24:40.613 --> 24:42.281
I'm pretty easygoing,

24:42.314 --> 24:44.150
but you're approaching
insubordination.

24:46.085 --> 24:47.654
You're gonna report me?

24:47.687 --> 24:49.722
I'm not gonna
report anybody.

24:49.756 --> 24:51.023
But maybe next time,
try not to have

24:51.057 --> 24:53.693
such a stick up your ass
about being asked out.

24:53.726 --> 25:00.667
**

25:00.700 --> 25:01.634
Oh, come on.

25:01.668 --> 25:03.670
I always thought Bunny
was the cutest nickname.

25:03.703 --> 25:05.672
Of course you did, but you
could've stopped calling me that

25:05.705 --> 25:07.940
when I was 12
or -- or 20.

25:07.974 --> 25:10.076
[ Chuckles ]

25:10.109 --> 25:11.978
Rough day?

25:14.346 --> 25:17.617
Yeah.
Yeah, it was something.

25:17.650 --> 25:20.219
Well, this should make you
a little happier.

25:20.252 --> 25:23.956
I have decided to take care
of your entire wedding.

25:23.990 --> 25:25.592
We don't need it.

25:26.959 --> 25:28.260
You're welcome.

25:28.294 --> 25:29.361
We're not 21.

25:29.395 --> 25:32.098
We're more than capable
of paying for our own wedding.

25:32.131 --> 25:33.833
We make good money.

25:33.866 --> 25:37.003
But you won't once you start
having kids, Bunny.

25:41.173 --> 25:43.542
[ Sighs ]

25:46.012 --> 25:48.114
[ Door opens ]

25:52.018 --> 25:55.622
What are you
doing in here?

25:55.655 --> 25:58.725
I'm hiding
from my therapist.

25:58.758 --> 26:02.862
I am not going to get
a surround-sound speaker system.

26:02.895 --> 26:05.898
But I am doing whatever
the hell I feel like doing.

26:05.932 --> 26:07.099
Mm-hmm.

26:07.133 --> 26:08.801
Can you hand me that mop?

26:08.835 --> 26:10.269
Hmm, okay.

26:16.643 --> 26:20.747
Are you satisfied with what
you've done with your life?

26:22.649 --> 26:25.251
Would you be happy
if you died tomorrow?

26:25.284 --> 26:28.020
Uh, satisfied?

26:28.054 --> 26:30.156
Happy?

26:30.189 --> 26:35.094
[ Chuckles ] I mean,
I clean up a building, uh...

26:35.127 --> 26:37.296
But I -- I married
the love of my life.

26:37.329 --> 26:41.333
Uh, we raised
three beautiful kids.

26:41.367 --> 26:46.038
One of them had some troubles,
but she's doing great now.

26:46.072 --> 26:49.642
The other two are doing
all right for themselves.

26:49.676 --> 26:51.711
And I was good to people.

26:51.744 --> 26:53.813
At least I think I was.

26:56.048 --> 26:58.350
That's a very good answer.

27:02.121 --> 27:04.323
I got pictures of the girls
if you want see --

27:04.356 --> 27:05.958
No.

27:07.794 --> 27:10.396
So, why do I need to quit my job
to have a family?

27:10.429 --> 27:11.363
Agreed.

27:11.397 --> 27:13.966
She can be a great lawyer
and a great mom.

27:14.000 --> 27:16.435
Yes, she can, but why?

27:16.468 --> 27:20.039
[ Scoffs ]
W-Why waste your time working?

27:20.072 --> 27:22.208
You should be enjoying life,
like me.

27:22.241 --> 27:23.810
There's plenty
in the family trust.

27:23.843 --> 27:26.278
Dad, my work is important.
I'm helping people --

27:26.312 --> 27:28.981
Bunny...
you're pushing papers.

27:29.015 --> 27:31.317
How -- How is that really
helping anyone?

27:31.350 --> 27:33.185
And maybe I'm old-fashioned,
but I don't get it.

27:33.219 --> 27:35.087
I-I thought you were smarter
than that.

27:35.121 --> 27:36.823
You'd prefer her
to be a lazy parasite

27:36.856 --> 27:38.157
living off a trust fund

27:38.190 --> 27:40.760
as opposed to actually
contributing to society?

27:40.793 --> 27:42.094
Parasite?

27:42.128 --> 27:44.030
[ Silverware clacking ]

27:44.063 --> 27:46.332
My father made
a lot of money.

27:46.365 --> 27:48.701
I'm not going
to apologize for that.

27:48.735 --> 27:50.870
He made sure his children
and his grandchildren

27:50.903 --> 27:53.139
could enjoy their lives.

27:53.172 --> 27:54.406
I'm not hurting anyone.

27:54.440 --> 27:58.377
In fact, I go out of my way
to help people.

27:58.410 --> 28:01.147
So I'm sorry if that
doesn't qualify me

28:01.180 --> 28:03.449
as a worthwhile person
in your book.

28:06.252 --> 28:08.054
I'll get the check
on my way out.

28:08.087 --> 28:11.090
Dad,
you don't have to...

28:24.036 --> 28:25.337
[ Sighs ]

28:31.911 --> 28:34.180
[ Door opens ]

28:37.516 --> 28:39.318
What am I doing wrong,
Shaun?

28:40.386 --> 28:42.421
I don't know.

28:46.458 --> 28:49.495
I tried...

28:49.528 --> 28:51.530
encouraging,
I've tried being supportive,

28:51.563 --> 28:52.899
I've tried bribing you.

28:52.932 --> 28:56.903
I don't need a therapist.
No.

28:56.936 --> 28:59.005
Look around you.
What -- You're sleeping --

28:59.038 --> 29:01.874
What is this,
a broom closet?

29:01.908 --> 29:04.844
Look at the sacrifices
you're willing to make

29:04.877 --> 29:06.913
just to avoid...

29:08.447 --> 29:13.485
**

29:13.519 --> 29:15.521
We're gonna
pick this up later.

29:19.125 --> 29:21.160
You have to file a complaint
with HR.

29:21.193 --> 29:24.296
I do that and I get labeled
"hostile" and "difficult,"

29:24.330 --> 29:26.866
neither of which work
with my complexion or gender.

29:26.899 --> 29:28.434
All the more reason
to take a stand.

29:28.467 --> 29:31.037
Claire, this situation
is exactly what HR is for.

29:31.070 --> 29:32.471
[ Chuckles ]
I didn't say it was easy.

29:32.504 --> 29:33.873
Yeah, you did.

29:33.906 --> 29:35.574
Look, it's scary
and it takes courage,

29:35.607 --> 29:38.077
but it's the right thing
to do.
It's a pointless thing
to do.

29:38.110 --> 29:40.913
They'll listen to you.
They will shift the blame
onto me.

29:40.947 --> 29:42.481
Like you did.

29:42.514 --> 29:43.482
Whoa, what?
How did I --

29:43.515 --> 29:45.584
I came to you,
you accused me of exaggerating

29:45.617 --> 29:46.652
to get back onto the case.

29:46.685 --> 29:48.454
No, no, no, that's not
what I meant. I had no idea --

29:48.487 --> 29:50.122
I said
he was too friendly.

29:50.156 --> 29:53.225
You said he was "trying
to establish a rapport."

29:54.526 --> 29:56.328
I'm sleeping with you,
Jared,

29:56.362 --> 29:58.130
and you thought
I was overreacting.

29:58.164 --> 30:00.933
How do you think three strangers
will see things?

30:05.571 --> 30:07.473
Claire, I'm sorry.
I am so sorry.

30:07.506 --> 30:10.076
Don't worry about it.
It's just the way it is.

30:10.109 --> 30:11.911
I've got a patient
to round on.

30:14.046 --> 30:16.582
Dr. Melendez
and I had a talk

30:16.615 --> 30:19.218
and we believe
we can excise the tumor

30:19.251 --> 30:21.888
if you're willing
to make a sacrifice.

30:21.921 --> 30:24.556
Sacrifice?

30:24.590 --> 30:26.058
That sounds better
than death.

30:26.092 --> 30:28.494
My thinking as well.

30:28.527 --> 30:30.562
We believe we can
remove the mass,

30:30.596 --> 30:34.000
but we'll also have to take
a piece out of your brain stem.

30:34.033 --> 30:35.367
A chunk
of the red nucleus,

30:35.401 --> 30:38.370
which helps control
the left side of your body.

30:38.404 --> 30:41.373
You'll be paralyzed
on that side.

30:41.407 --> 30:43.475
It could also result
in difficulty

30:43.509 --> 30:45.644
eating and swallowing.

30:45.677 --> 30:47.947
Speech difficulties.

30:52.118 --> 30:53.419
Let's do it.

30:53.452 --> 30:55.221
Good for you.

30:57.056 --> 30:58.557
Andrews:
Hold on. Hold on.

30:58.590 --> 31:01.393
Bobby,
this is very risky surgery.

31:01.427 --> 31:04.130
You could die on the table,
and even if all goes well,

31:04.163 --> 31:06.098
you will be
severely disabled.

31:06.132 --> 31:09.235
Yeah, I -- I was listening,
and I'm in.

31:09.268 --> 31:11.170
[ Sighs ]

31:18.444 --> 31:21.981
Guys, hey, I get it.

31:22.014 --> 31:25.451
If I'm dead,
I'm -- I'm dead.

31:25.484 --> 31:30.990
But if not -- PT,
relearning stuff, whatever.

31:31.023 --> 31:34.360
It's not gonna stop me
from competing.

31:34.393 --> 31:36.562
Not ever.

31:36.595 --> 31:40.132
Bobby,
your career is over.

31:40.166 --> 31:42.168
We need you
to understand that.

31:49.708 --> 31:51.077
Yeah?

31:59.551 --> 32:01.988
Once a gamer,
always a gamer, huh?

32:03.422 --> 32:05.491
You got my respect.

32:14.333 --> 32:17.269
**

32:17.303 --> 32:19.138
[ Locker door closes ]

32:23.175 --> 32:24.243
What the hell
is your problem?

32:24.276 --> 32:25.978
If you ever
threaten Claire,

32:26.012 --> 32:26.945
take
a disrespectful tone,

32:26.979 --> 32:29.481
or so much as look at her
cross-eyed again,

32:29.515 --> 32:30.983
I'm gonna do
a hell of a lot more

32:31.017 --> 32:32.484
than put you up
against a wall.

32:32.518 --> 32:33.752
We clear?

32:33.785 --> 32:40.426
**

32:40.459 --> 32:45.497
**

32:45.531 --> 32:49.368
Your lungs are looking
a lot better.

32:49.401 --> 32:53.505
Overall,
you're in pretty good shape.

32:53.539 --> 32:55.574
[ Coughs ]

32:59.745 --> 33:01.413
Thank you.

33:01.447 --> 33:03.182
You're welcome.

33:03.215 --> 33:05.651
All part of the service.

33:05.684 --> 33:09.655
And good for you.

33:09.688 --> 33:12.358
I wasn't sleeping.

33:12.391 --> 33:15.194
I heard the way
you handled that other doctor.

33:17.063 --> 33:20.099
You heard that?
All of it?

33:21.667 --> 33:24.136
I wish I had done that.

33:24.170 --> 33:25.537
You were brave.

33:25.571 --> 33:29.341
No, no.

33:29.375 --> 33:31.277
If I was brave, I --

33:31.310 --> 33:38.050
**

33:38.084 --> 33:40.286
[ Monitor beeping ]

33:40.319 --> 33:42.521
Glassman: Rick Allen.

33:42.554 --> 33:44.456
Who?
One-armed drummer
for Def Leppard.

33:44.490 --> 33:46.158
Come on, man.

33:46.192 --> 33:49.561
And there
is the tumor capsule.

33:49.595 --> 33:52.564
Richie Parker.
Anyone?

33:52.598 --> 33:55.567
Isn't he a NASCAR guy?
An engineer, right?

33:55.601 --> 33:56.702
Born without arms?

33:56.735 --> 33:59.705
And Nurse Ocampo
gets the door prize.

33:59.738 --> 34:02.408
And now we will take
just a little piece

34:02.441 --> 34:06.712
of our friend here --
a nice sample to test.

34:06.745 --> 34:08.447
Thank you, Doctor.

34:08.480 --> 34:09.381
And now the rest.

34:09.415 --> 34:11.250
He may not be able
to tie his own shoes,

34:11.283 --> 34:14.453
but I wouldn't bet against him
ever competing again.

34:14.486 --> 34:17.823
Aut libertatem
aut mortem mihi da.

34:17.856 --> 34:19.391
Shaun,
do you know that means?

34:19.425 --> 34:23.129
No. It's not relevant
to this surgery.

34:23.162 --> 34:25.331
Oh, it's relevant.
Look it up.

34:25.364 --> 34:26.432
No, it's not.

34:26.465 --> 34:31.203
Heart rate and ETCO2
are rising.

34:31.237 --> 34:32.871
Slight change
in body temperature.

34:32.904 --> 34:34.206
His heart rate's 108.

34:34.240 --> 34:35.674
Check tube placement
and suction him.

34:35.707 --> 34:38.177
If he takes a turn,
we might have to abort.

34:38.210 --> 34:40.279
I don't think so.
I'm too far in.

34:40.312 --> 34:41.313
Keep him stable.

34:41.347 --> 34:42.614
He's tachy.
Heart rate's climbing.

34:42.648 --> 34:46.352
115, 117, 120,
and rising.

34:46.385 --> 34:49.488
He is going into v-tach.
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

34:49.521 --> 34:50.756
Robert Ato is dying.

34:56.295 --> 34:58.630
I'm gonna pull out
of the pons slowly.
Well, hold on.

34:58.664 --> 35:00.532
You pull out now, you might
damage the cerebellar peduncle.

35:00.566 --> 35:03.402
If I don't get out now, I'll
kill him if he starts seizing.

35:03.435 --> 35:05.671
Something's not right.
Tachycardia?

35:05.704 --> 35:07.673
Bradycardia
would make more sense.

35:09.841 --> 35:11.710
Ideas.
-Anyone?

35:13.745 --> 35:14.646
Tell me what you see.

35:14.680 --> 35:17.883
Tachycardia, rising body
temperature again,

35:17.916 --> 35:20.686
muscle rigidity,
CO2 is rising.

35:20.719 --> 35:22.321
Muscle rigidity?
Which side?

35:22.354 --> 35:23.522
It's all over.

35:23.555 --> 35:24.790
Then it's not
the brain stem.

35:24.823 --> 35:26.692
We'd only have muscle rigidity
on one side.

35:26.725 --> 35:31.730
Think.
Tachycardia, rising temp, CO2...

35:31.763 --> 35:33.399
CO2...

35:33.432 --> 35:34.533
It's the anesthesia.

35:34.566 --> 35:36.535
Malignant hyperthermia.
Get the MH cart.

35:36.568 --> 35:37.936
140 dantrolene, STAT.

35:37.969 --> 35:39.838
Kalu, Murphy, get as many
cooling blankets as you can.

35:39.871 --> 35:40.939
We need to get
this temperature down.

35:40.972 --> 35:41.940
-Coming out.
-Now!

35:41.973 --> 35:44.176
Hyperventilate
at 100% O2,

35:44.210 --> 35:45.177
10 liters per minute.

35:45.211 --> 35:47.613
Flush out the old anesthetic,
lower the ETCO2.

35:47.646 --> 35:49.748
I want vecuronium on deck.
We got to keep him under.

35:49.781 --> 35:50.749
Let's move!

35:50.782 --> 35:56.555
**

35:56.588 --> 35:57.889
And we're on.

35:57.923 --> 35:58.957
[ Beeping continues ]

35:58.990 --> 36:00.326
Uh, temp's
not coming down.

36:00.359 --> 36:01.593
Wait.

36:01.627 --> 36:03.595
[ Beeping continues ]

36:03.629 --> 36:05.864
**

36:05.897 --> 36:08.334
[ Beeping slows ]

36:08.367 --> 36:09.835
CO2 is coming down.

36:09.868 --> 36:11.703
Heart rate
is coming down, too.

36:11.737 --> 36:14.273
Temperature is 101.

36:14.306 --> 36:16.408
Okay.
Nice work, everyone.

36:16.442 --> 36:19.311
Thank you very much.

36:19.345 --> 36:21.313
Terry Fox.

36:21.347 --> 36:24.516
Or my personal favorite --
Jim Abbott.

36:24.550 --> 36:29.455
**

36:29.488 --> 36:34.726
**

36:34.760 --> 36:36.462
[ Knock on door ]
Come in.

36:36.495 --> 36:38.764
[ Door opens ]

36:38.797 --> 36:40.766
Hi.

36:40.799 --> 36:44.903
I need to talk to you
about Dr. Coyle.

36:48.039 --> 36:50.742
Dr. Browne.

36:50.776 --> 36:53.779
I wanted to talk to you
about the same thing.

36:53.812 --> 36:55.481
Please.

36:55.514 --> 37:02.721
**

37:05.557 --> 37:09.495
The surgery
was a success.

37:09.528 --> 37:13.031
And the outcome
might be better than expected.

37:13.064 --> 37:15.367
There will still be significant
neurological dysfunction

37:15.401 --> 37:18.704
on your left side, but not
as much as we'd anticipated.

37:18.737 --> 37:21.273
[ Slowly ] Sick!

37:22.441 --> 37:25.311
[ Inhales deeply ]
Thank you.

37:25.344 --> 37:27.279
You did good,
my friend.

37:37.589 --> 37:40.592
You have to be patient.

37:40.626 --> 37:43.495
Nah.

37:43.529 --> 37:47.699
Is patience a bad thing?

37:47.733 --> 37:54.573
[ Slowly ]
Acceptance is a bad thing.

37:54.606 --> 37:56.575
[ Chuckles ]

37:56.608 --> 38:03.549
When I was a kid, I --
I wasn't good at jack.

38:03.582 --> 38:07.953
But I never quit.

38:07.986 --> 38:12.558
I...

38:12.591 --> 38:15.394
found my thing.

38:17.363 --> 38:21.767
Don't ever let
anyone tell you

38:21.800 --> 38:27.606
what you can
and can't...

38:27.639 --> 38:29.107
do.

38:29.140 --> 38:39.117
**

38:39.150 --> 38:49.127
**

38:49.160 --> 38:55.667
**

38:55.701 --> 38:59.538
I'm sorry.
For last night.

38:59.571 --> 39:02.007
It was a rough day.
I was tired.

39:02.040 --> 39:05.010
Probably had a few too...

39:05.043 --> 39:07.946
Your relationship with
your father is your business --

39:07.979 --> 39:10.015
Neil, you don't have to.
[ Chuckles ]

39:10.048 --> 39:16.622
**

39:16.655 --> 39:18.624
I'll call your dad,
and --

39:18.657 --> 39:21.760
I don't want to have kids.

39:21.793 --> 39:26.865
**

39:26.898 --> 39:32.070
**

39:37.443 --> 39:40.111
Shaun,
I'm gonna drive you home.

39:40.145 --> 39:41.747
You're gonna see Melissa.

39:41.780 --> 39:43.849
If you don't like her,
she'll leave.

39:43.882 --> 39:46.985
But there's no more
running away.

39:47.018 --> 39:49.855
Why do you think
I'm doing this?

39:49.888 --> 39:52.624
Because you are stubborn.

39:52.658 --> 39:55.193
Ok-Okay, yeah, okay, sure.
I'm stubborn.

39:55.226 --> 39:57.796
But I'm doing this for you,
okay?

39:57.829 --> 39:59.097
So that you can
have a better life,

39:59.130 --> 40:02.133
so that you can
have a happier life.

40:02.167 --> 40:05.671
What if it doesn't
make me happy?

40:05.704 --> 40:07.573
What if it doesn't
make me happy?

40:07.606 --> 40:11.510
What if it only
makes you happy?

40:11.543 --> 40:14.145
You think -- You think
I'm doing this to make me happy?

40:14.179 --> 40:15.981
I'm not happy, Shaun.

40:16.014 --> 40:18.917
I'm not close to being happy,
and you know what?

40:18.950 --> 40:20.686
I am done explaining,

40:20.719 --> 40:23.589
I am done bribing,
and I am done talking.

40:23.622 --> 40:24.690
Now let's go.
No. N-No.

40:24.723 --> 40:26.224
No! Let's go!
No!

40:26.257 --> 40:27.726
No.

40:27.759 --> 40:31.162
No, I -- I want to make
my own decisions.

40:31.196 --> 40:32.931
I --
Shaun, can you keep
your voice down, please? Please?

40:32.964 --> 40:36.067
You -- You cannot keep
ordering me around, okay?

40:36.101 --> 40:37.869
You're not my father!

40:37.903 --> 40:39.638
[ Exhales deeply ]

40:39.671 --> 40:41.206
I know that.

40:41.239 --> 40:43.809
Shaun,
I don't understand...

40:43.842 --> 40:45.944
Okay.
...why this is so upsetting.

40:45.977 --> 40:47.713
You don't let anyone --
I don't get it.

40:47.746 --> 40:52.751
anyone ever tell you
what you can and can't do.
Shaun, let's just calm down now,
please.

40:52.784 --> 40:55.721
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.
Okay, don't let anyone ever tell
you what you can and can't do!

40:55.754 --> 40:58.590
Hey, just calm --
Shaun. Hey, hey, Shaun.
I want to make
my own decisions.

40:58.624 --> 41:00.191
Okay, okay, okay.
I want to make
my own decisions!

41:00.225 --> 41:02.193
I'm just trying to help.
I want make my own --

41:02.227 --> 41:03.529
Shaun!
I don't want help!

41:03.562 --> 41:04.996
[ Breathing heavily ]

41:05.030 --> 41:06.865
I --

41:06.898 --> 41:15.140
**

41:17.909 --> 41:19.645
What were you thinking?!

41:19.678 --> 41:21.780
I do not need you
to fight my battles,

41:21.813 --> 41:24.516
and I certainly never
asked you to.

41:24.550 --> 41:26.217
And if you really
respected me,

41:26.251 --> 41:28.219
you would not treat me
like some damsel

41:28.253 --> 41:29.588
who needed protection,
okay?

41:29.621 --> 41:31.022
You would treat me
with the respect

41:31.056 --> 41:33.525
that you would automatically
give to a man.

41:33.559 --> 41:34.693
You'd treat me
like a person

41:34.726 --> 41:37.629
capable of handling
her own life!

41:37.663 --> 41:40.298
And maybe -- maybe it's too much
to ask of you.

41:40.331 --> 41:44.269
Apparently Andrews
agrees with you.

41:44.302 --> 41:45.571
I've just been fired

41:45.604 --> 41:47.305
for physically assaulting
an employee.

41:47.338 --> 41:51.977
**

41:52.010 --> 41:53.278
[ Knock on door ]

41:53.311 --> 41:56.682
Shaun? Shaun!

41:56.715 --> 41:58.049
Where would he go?

41:58.083 --> 41:59.851
Is there a place
he likes to hang out,

41:59.885 --> 42:00.919
a place where he feels
comfortable?

42:00.952 --> 42:02.654
[ Sighs ]
No, I don't know.

42:02.688 --> 42:05.023
I mean, he's not
at the hospital.

42:05.056 --> 42:09.961
And there used to be
a picture here of Shaun...

42:09.995 --> 42:12.564
[sighs]
and his brother, Steve.

42:14.099 --> 42:15.801
What do you think
that means?

42:15.834 --> 42:21.907
**

42:21.940 --> 42:24.142
It means
he's not coming back.

42:30.115 --> 42:38.156
**

42:38.189 --> 42:46.264
**

42:46.297 --> 42:54.339
**

42:54.372 --> 43:02.681
**
